## The spine (intent-named)
```
0-context/    what frames the work ({{CONTEXT_TITLE}}: scope/role, goals)
1-inbox/      raw inputs (transcripts, notes, reference, from-brain)
2-work/       your deliverables / drafts
3-log/        decisions, tasks, hours
4-shared/     what you've promoted outward ({{OUTWARD_DESC}})
5-personal/   your private scratch (never syncs)
.claude/      the agent layer: skills, rules, rubrics, memory
```

## Working here
- Log decisions in `3-log/decision-log.md` (see `.claude/rules/decision-log.md`).
- Track time in `3-log/hours-log.md`.
- Promote work via the flow in `.claude/rules/publishing.md`.
- Run the harnesses in `.claude/skills/` (decision-audit, scope-creep, weekly-synthesis).
- Validate with the AIOS Workspace validators.

## Team Brain (optional)
Sync tier-tagged content to an AIOS Team Brain. Configure `aios.yaml` (right
here, at the root of *this* workspace — it's a real, already-generated file,
not a template) + `.env` (see `.env.example`), then:
```
npm run aios -- status   # what would sync (and what's blocked, and why)
npm run aios -- push     # push team/{{OUTWARD_TIER}}-tier content
npm run aios -- pull     # fetch team updates into 1-inbox/from-brain/
npm run aios -- query "what did we decide about X?"
```
The shim in `scripts/aios.mjs` forwards to the toolkit clone — set `AIOS_TOOLKIT_CLI` if it is not on a default relative path.
`private` and untagged content never leave this machine.
